But all was about to change with the idea that the man had been struck by.

00:01:44.528 --> 00:01:49.301
He would create a huge fictional world based in 19th century France.

00:01:49.738 --> 00:01:53.728
He would write stories about the characters that existed in this world.

00:01:54.428 --> 00:02:00.718
Each book would focus on the trials and tribulations of a different character, but there would be

00:02:00.728 --> 00:02:07.008
some overlap - the main character in one book might be a minor character in another, and so on.

00:02:07.958 --> 00:02:14.678
He ran to his sister’s apartment, declaring “I’m about to become a genius”, and he got to work.

00:02:15.778 --> 00:02:21.098
In the next 18 years he would go on to write almost 100 books about this

00:02:21.108 --> 00:02:26.658
fictional world, before dropping over and dying from a heart attack aged 51.

00:02:27.812 --> 00:02:34.972
The man was Honoré de Balzac, and his fictional world was La Comédie Humaine, the Human Comedy.

00:02:36.422 --> 00:02:42.557
Fast forward a few hundred years and anyone going to any cinema, almost anywhere

